events.name: Charlotte Hornets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 23 points, five rebounds and five assists, and the New York Knicks scored a season-high in their 129-107 win over the Charlotte Hornets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks record season-highs in points, shooting percentage in 129-107 win over Hornets

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges' shot was off, two fellow starters just got back and two others are still out.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges scores 27 points, helps Nets recover after blowing big lead to beat Wizards 102-94

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 27 points and the Memphis Grizzlies won for the second time this season, beating the reeling Los...
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane scores 27 points, Grizzlies survive Clippers' 4th-quarter charge for 2nd win, 105-101

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey scored a career-high 50 points, Joel Embiid had 37 points and the Philadelphia 76ers improved to 8-1 with their eighth straight victory, beating the Indiana Pacers 137-126 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Maxey scores career-high 50 points, leads 76ers to 8th straight win

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 29 points, Nikola Vucevic added 21 points and 12 rebounds and the Chicago Bulls beat the Detroit Pistons 119-108 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 29 points as Bulls beat Pistons 119-108

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 26 points and Alperen Sengun added 23 to lead the Houston Rockets to a 107-104 win over the Denver Nuggets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fred VanVleet leads Rockets to sixth straight victory with 107-104 win over Nuggets

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving made 7 of 10 3-pointers and scored 35 points, Luka Doncic had 15 of his 30 points in a 42-point third quarter and the Dallas Mavericks beat the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans 136-124 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving hits 7 of 10 3-pointers, scores 35 points in Mavericks' 136-124 victory over Pelicans

events.name: Miami Heat at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — The Miami Heat were short-handed, playing the second night of a back-to-back and playing against the most hyped prospect in decades in San Antonio Spurs rookie Victor Wembanyama.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robinson, Adebayo key rally as Heat capture fifth straight with win over Spurs, 118-113

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 35 points, Jalen Williams had 31 and the Oklahoma City Thunder used a big fourth quarter to beat the Phoenix Suns 111-99 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Thunder storm ahead in 4th quarter, beat Suns 111-99

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Coach Chris Finch just talked to his Minnesota Timberwolves the other day about finding ways to make strides and improve doing the small things even while winning.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards, Towns lead Timberwolves past Curry and Warriors, 116-110

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 30 points and 13 rebounds, Rui Hachimura scored eight of his 19 points in the final 3:43 and the Los Angeles Lakers overcame LeBron James' injury absence to beat the Portland Trail Blazers 116-110 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron sits with injury while Davis, Hachimura propel Lakers to 116-110 win over Trail Blazers
